==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Angola pea
<hw>An*go"la pea`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A tropical
plant (<spn>Cajanus indicus</spn>) and its edible seed, a kind of pulse;
-- so called from <ets>Angola</ets> in Western Africa. Called also
<altname>pigeon pea</altname> and <altname>Congo
pea</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Angolese</ent>⟦br⟧
